Class CircularQueue

java.lang.Object
edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.queue.AbstractQueue
edu.sru.thangiah.datastructures.queue.CircularQueue
All Implemented Interfaces:
BaseOpsInt, ListOpsInt
public class CircularQueue extends AbstractQueue

Title: CircularQueue

Description:

A circular queue is a data structure in which the last position in the queue is linked to the first position hence the circular nature. With a normal queue we may run into issues of maximizing our queue's capacity since elements de-queued are left uninitialized and still take up space in the queue. The usefulness of a circular queue solves this issue since we always have a pointer to the front and rear of the container.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Sam R. Thangiah
